<bug>
	<id>21938</id>
	<title>Docker image specification should be updated for content addressability</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">The image spec at https://github.com/docker/docker/blob/3d13fddd2bc4d679f0eaa68b0be877e5a816ad53/image/spec/v1.md hasn't been updated for the content addressability changes that went into Docker 1.10.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.2">This spec also seems to contain some outdated fields like "image checksum".</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.3">It shouldn't be very hard to bring this up to date.</sentence>
			<sentence id="1.4">The changes in 1.10 are described in https://gist.github.com/aaronlehmann/b42a2eaf633fc949f93b#new-image-config.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">cc @stevvooe @tonistiigi @dmcgowan</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
